quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  11,61,"And to Thamood their brother Salih; he said, 'O my people, serve God! You have no god other than He. It is He who produced you from the earth and has given you to live therein; so ask forgiveness of Him, then repent to Him; surely my Lord is nigh, and answers prayer"
  11,62,"They said, 'Salih, thou hast hitherto been a source of hope among us. What, dost thou forbid us to serve that our fathers served? Truly we are in doubt, concerning what thou callest us to, disquieting"
  11,63,"He said, 'O my people, what think you? If I stand upon a clear sign from my Lord, and He has given me mercy from Him, who shall help me against God if I rebel against Him? You would do nothing for me, except increase my loss"
  11,64,"O my people, this is the She-camel of God, to be a sign for you. Leave her that she may eat in God's earth, and touch her not with evil, lest you' be seized by a nigh chastisement"
  11,65,"But they hamstrung her; and he said, 'Take your joy in your habitation three days -- that is a promise not to be belied"
  11,66,"And when Our command came, We delivered Salih and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us, and from the degradation of that day; thy Lord is the All-strong, the All-mighty"
  11,67,"And the evildoers were seized by the Cry, and morning found them in their habitations fallen prostrate"
  11,68,"as if they never dwelt there: 'Surely Thamood disbelieved in their Lord, so away with Thamood"
  11,69,"Our messengers came to Abraham with the good tidings; they said, 'Peace!' 'Peace,' he said; and presently he brought a roasted calf"
  11,70,"And when he saw their hands not reaching towards it, he was suspicious of them and conceived a fear of them. They said, 'Fear not; we have been sent to the people of Lot"
  11,71,"And his wife was standing by; she laughed, therefore We gave her the glad tidings of Isaac, and, after Isaac, of Jacob"
  11,72,"She said, 'Woe is me! Shall I bear, being an old woman, and this my husband is an old man? This assuredly is a strange thing"
  11,73,"They said, 'What, dost thou marvel at God's command? The mercy of God and His blessings be upon you, O people of the House! Surely He is All-laudable, All-glorious"
  11,74,"So, when the awe departed from Abraham and the good tidings came to him, he was disputing with Us concerning the people of Lot"
  11,75,"Abraham was clement, compassionate, penitent"
  11,76,"O Abraham, turn away from this; thy Lord's command has surely come, and there is coming upon them a chastisement not to be turned back"
  11,77,"And when Our messengers came to Lot, he was troubled on their account and distressed for them, and he said, 'This is a fierce day"
  11,78,"And his people came to him, running towards him; and erstwhile they had been doing evil deeds. He said, 'O my people, these are my daughters; they are cleaner for you. So fear God, and do not degrade me in my guests. What, is there not one man among you of a right mind"
  11,79,"They said, 'Thou knowest we have no right to thy daughters, and thou well knowest what we desire"
  11,80,"He said, 'O would that I had power against you, or might take refuge in a strong pillar"
  11,81,"They said, 'Lot, we are messengers of thy Lord. They shall not reach thee; so set forth, thou with thy family, in a watch of the night, and let not any one of you turn round, excepting thy wife; surely she shall be smitten by that which smites them. Their promised time is the morning; is the morning not nigh"
  11,82,"So when Our command came, We turned it uppermost nethermost, and rained on it stones of baked clay, one on another"
  11,83,"marked with thy Lord, and never far from the evildoers"